[[File:Pier Blankenberge R02.jpg|thumb|De pier van Blankenberge vanuit zee]]
The '''Belgium Pier''' is a pier in [[Blankenberge]], Belgium. It was built in 1933 after an [[Art Deco]] design by architect Jules Soete. The concrete structure stretches 350 meters out into the North Sea. The Belgium Pier replaced an earlier structure that was the first pier at the Atlantic and North Sea costs of the European continent, and the only other pier like it is the [[Scheveningen Pier]] in the Netherlands.
[[File:Belgium Pier from Blankenberge Beach in 2017 duotone.jpg|thumb|Belgium Pier 2017]]

