{{for|the airport serving [[São Pedro, São Paulo|São Pedro]], [[Brazil]]|São Pedro Airport (Brazil)}} {{Infobox airport | name = Cesária Évora Airport | nativename = {{small|''Aeroporto Internacional Cesária Évora''}} | nativename-a = | nativename-r = | image = AeroportoSPedro.JPG | image-width = 250 | IATA = VXE | ICAO = GVSV | type = Public | owner = | operator = Aeroportos Segurança Aérea (ASA) | city-served = [[Mindelo]] | location = [[São Vicente, Cape Verde|São Vicente]], [[Cape Verde]] | hub = [[TACV Cabo Verde Airlines]] | metric-elev = yes | metric-rwy = yes | elevation-m = 20 | coordinates = {{coord|16|49|59.16|N|25|3|24.84|W|region:CV|display=inline,title}} | website = {{URL|http://www.caboverde.com/ilhas/s-vicen/tacv.htm}} | pushpin_map = Cape Verde | pushpin_label = VXE | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Cape Verde | r1-number = 07/25 | r1-length-m = 1,975 | r1-surface = [[Asphalt]] | stat-year = 2017 | stat1-header = Passengers | stat1-data = 266,221 | stat2-header = Operations | stat2-data = 5,146 | stat3-header = Metric [[tonnes]] of cargo | stat3-data = 377<ref name="2017 data">{{cite web|url=https://www.asa.cv/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Boletim-de-Trafego-Ano-2017.pdf|title=Boletim Estatístico de Tráfego – Ano 2017|publisher=ASA|language=pt|date=January 2018|accessdate=27 September 2018|deadurl=no|archiveurl=|archivedate=|df=}}</ref> }}
'''Cesária Évora Airport''' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] '''''Aeroporto Internacional Cesária Évora''''') {{Airport codes|VXE|GVSV}} is [[Cape Verde]]'s third most-used [[airport]] located on the [[island]] of [[São Vicente, Cape Verde|São Vicente]], located nearly {{convert|5|km|mi}} from the centre of [[Mindelo]]. It is located in the valley area in the west of the island and is north of the village of [[São Pedro, Cape Verde|São Pedro]]. Its runway is {{convert|1975|m|ft}} long and its width is {{convert|45|m|ft}}.
==History== The airport was constructed in 1959-1960. It was expanded to be able to host international flights between 2005 and 2009. The airport was officially renamed after the highly acclaimed singer [[Cesária Évora]] in 2012.<ref name=dgt>[http://www.portaldoconhecimento.gov.cv/bitstream/10961/4126/1/IRTUR2_SV%20final.pdf Inventário dos recursos turísticos do município de S. Vicente], Direcção Geral do Turismo, p. 63</ref> It has a modern terminal of about {{convert|11000|m2|ft2}} and has the capacity to process about 500 passengers an hour.{{cn|date=September 2018}}
==Airlines and destinations== {{Airport-dest-list <!-- --> |[[Binter Canarias]]| [[Nelson Mandela International Airport|Praia]], [[Amílcar Cabral International Airport|Sal]] <!-- --> |[[Cabo Verde Express]]| '''Charter:''' [[Amílcar Cabral International Airport|Sal]] <!-- --> |[[TAP Air Portugal]]| [[Lisbon Portela Airport|Lisbon]] <!-- --> |[[TUI fly Netherlands]]|[[Amsterdam Airport Schiphol|Amsterdam]] <!-- --> }}
==Statistics== In 2017, the annual passenger number was 266,221, of which 82,892 on international flights. There were 5,146 air operations, of which 780 international. {{convert|377|t|LT ST}} of cargo were transported, of which 227 international.<ref name="2017 data"/>
