'''Cape Verde''' elects on national level a [[head of state]] - the [[president]] - and a [[legislature]]. The president is elected for a five-year term by the people. The [[National Assembly of Cape Verde|National Assembly]] ({{lang-pt|Assembleia Nacional}}) has 72 members, elected for a five-year term by [[proportional representation]]. Cape Verde has a [[two-party system]], which means that there are two dominant [[political parties]], with extreme difficulty for anybody to achieve electoral success under the banner of any other party.
