'''Ethnos''' ({{lang-el|Έθνος|lit="The Nation"}}) is the name of a [[Greece|Greek]] daily newspaper first published in 1930.
{{Infobox Newspaper | name = Ethnos | logo = | image = Εθνος.jpg | image_size = 220px | caption = | type = daily newspaper | format = | foundation = {{start date|1930}} | price = | publisher = [[Ivan Savvidis|Dimera Media Investments]] | editor = | chiefeditor = | assoceditor = | staff = | language = Greek | political = Centre, Centre-left | circulation = | publishing_city = [[Athens]] | publishing_country = Greece | oclc = | ISSN = | website = {{Official URL}} }}
==History== The newspaper was first published in 1930. In 1970, during the [[Greek military junta of 1967-74]], it was forced to stop publishing. In 1981, [[Dimitris Varos]] relaunched it as a colour tabloid.
The newspaper was owned for years by Pegasus Publishing S.A.<ref>[http://www.helex.gr/en/web/guest/stock-company-profile/-/select-stock/815 Helex]</ref> In 2017 was sold to Dimera Media Investments, owned by [[Ivan Savvidis]].<ref>[http://www.tovima.gr/media/article/?aid=894212 Mε €3.580.000 ο Σαββίδης πήρε Εθνος, Εθνος Κυριακής και Ημερησία] tovima.gr, 29 Ιουλίου 2017</ref> Dimera reportedly acquired the two Ethnos titles (daily and Sunday) for 3 million euros.<ref>http://greece.greekreporter.com/2017/07/26/greek-russian-businessman-ivan-savvidis-buys-3-historic-newspapers/</ref>
