'''MontenegroSong''' was a pop festival in [[Montenegro]], whose winning song went to represent the country in the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. It was organized by [[RTCG]]. MontenegroSong's first edition was on February 25, 2007. The winner of the competition was decided through televoting. MontenegroSong was disestablished in 2008, after only 2 editions.
==History== The festival was founded as '''Montevizija''' in 2005. The winner of Europjesma was going to represent [[Serbia and Montenegro]] in the [[Eurovision Song Contest]]. Montevizija was organized by [[Radio-Television of Montenegro|RTCG]], the [[Montenegro|Montenegrin]] national broadcaster. The other semifinal was [[Beovizija]], organized by the Serbian broadcaster. The title MontenegroSong, was adopted in 2007.
