{{main|Military awards and decorations of Sri Lanka}} {{Infobox military award |name= Purna Bhumi Padakkama |image= Purna Bhumi medal.png |image_size= 140px |caption=Medal, reverse |awarded_by= [[Sri Lanka]] |type= Military decoration |eligibility= All ranks of the regular- and volunteer forces of the [[Military of Sri Lanka]] and service personnel of the [[Sri Lanka Police]] |for= Service |campaign= |status=Currently awarded |description= Suspended from a plain suspension bar |clasps= |established= 1977 |first_award= |last_award= |total= |posthumous= |recipients= |individual= |higher=[[North and East Operations Medal]] |same= |lower=[[Vadamarachchi Operation Medal]] |image2=[[File:Purna Bhumi Padakkama ribbon bar.svg|100px]] |caption2= [[Ribbon bar]] }}
The '''Purna Bhumi Padakkama''' ([[Sinhalese language|Sinhala]]: පූර්ණ භූමි පදක්කම ''pūrna bhūmi padakkama'') was a [[military decoration]] awarded by the [[Military of Sri Lanka]] (regular and volunteer) and [[Sri Lanka Police]] to all ranks of its forces in recognition of service in various districts that were regarded as theaters of the [[Sri Lankan Civil War]].
==Award process== For members of the [[Sri Lanka Navy]], this award was presented if they had served in<ref>{{cite web|title=Medal|url=http://www.navy.lk/en/medals-en.html|website=Sri Lanka Navy|publisher=navy.lk|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref>: * [[Jaffna District]] (since 22 July 1977), or * [[Vavuniya District]], [[Kilinochchi District]], [[Mullaitivu District]], [[Mannar District]], [[Batticaloa District]], [[Trincomalee District]] or [[Ampara District]] (since 16 September 1983). The [[Sri Lanka Army]] and [[Sri Lanka Air Force]] awarded the decorations for service in the same areas, with slightly different rules.<ref>{{cite web|title=Decorations & Medals|url=http://www.airforce.lk/pages.php?pages=decorations_medals|website=Sri Lanka Air Force|publisher=airforce.lk|accessdate=4 October 2017}}</ref>
==References== {{reflist}} *[http://www.navy.lk/gallery/medals/medals.htm Sri Lankan military awards and decorations]
==External links== *[http://www.army.lk/ Sri Lanka Army] *[http://www.navy.lk/ Sri Lanka Navy] *[http://www.airforce.lk/ Sri Lanka Air Force] *[http://www.police.lk/ Sri Lanka Police] *[http://www.defence.lk/ Ministry of Defence : Sri Lanka]
