{{ODM-stub}} {{Asia-mil-stub}} {{SriLanka-stub}}

'''Army Canal''' (Qanat al-Jaish in Arabic) ia a 25-kilometer waterway connecting the [[Tigris]] and [[Diyala River|Diyala]] rivers, forms the western boundary of [[Sadr City]], and when completed, will once again supply irrigation water to nearby agricultural areas and clean drinking water to [[Al-Rusafa, Iraq|Rusafa]], [[Baghdad]]. Also along its course a highway road runs.The Army Canal, which runs a total of 25 kilometers spanning from Adhamiyah in northeastern Baghdad to Rustimiyah in southeastern Baghdad, was built in 1959 by Abd al-Kassem Quassim, the former president of Iraq. It later became a ribbon of stagnant water and because of sludge, low water levels and lack of maintenance.

==References==
*[http://www.metimes.com/International/2008/12/02/iraqis_to_restore_baghdads_army_canal/8525/ Iraqis to Restore Baghdad's Army Canal]{{dead link|date=July 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}
* [http://newsblaze.com/story/20081202053158zmil.nb/topstory.html Major Iraqi-Led Project Begins With Army Canal Refurbishment]
* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090109014237/https://www.mnf-iraq.com/images/Unit_Newsletters/081216_aamalbinaa_english.pdf Major Iraqi-led project begins with Army Canal]

