{{Infobox diocese |jurisdiction = Diocese |name = Morombe |latin = Dioecesis Morombensis |country = Madagascar |metropolitan = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Toliara|Toliara]] |rite = [[Latin Rite]] |cathedral = |cocathedral = |area_km2 = 31,917 |population = 387,263 |population_as_of = 2002 |catholics = 31,206 |catholics_percent= 8.1 |pope = {{Incumbent pope}} |bishop = [[Zygmunt Robaszkiewicz]], [[Missionaries of the Holy Family|M.S.F.]] |coadjutor = |auxiliary_bishops= }}
The '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Morombe''' ([''[[Latin language|Latin]]: Moromben(sis)'') is a [[diocese]] located in the city of [[Morombe]] in the [[Ecclesiastical province]] of [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Toliara|Toliara]] in [[Madagascar]].
==History== * April 25, 1960: Established as Diocese of Morombe from the [[Diocese of Morondava]]
==Leadership== * [[Bishop]]s of Morombe (Roman rite) ** Bishop Zygmunt Robaszkiewicz, M.S.F. (since 2001.04.24) ** Bishop [[Alwin Albert Hafner]], M.S.F. (1989.05.15 – 2000.07.15) ** Bishop [[Joseph Zimmerman (bishop)|Joseph Zimmermann]], M.S.F. (1960.05.28 – 1988.12.04)
==See also== *[[Roman Catholicism in Madagascar]]
==Sources== * [http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/moro1.htm GCatholic.org] * [http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dmrmb.html Catholic Hierarchy]
